HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 850
By Martin B
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Huntingdon High
School football team, TSSAA Division I, Class
2A state champion.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Huntingdon High School football team achieved an extraordinary level
of success during the 2025 season, winning the coveted Tennessee Secondary School Athletic
Association (TSSAA) Division I, Class 2A State Football Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Huntingdon Mustangs claimed the title of state champion by defeating
reigning state champions Marion County High School by a score of 20-7 in the championship
game on December 6, 2025, at Finley Stadium in Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, on their path to the championship game, the Mustangs defeated Milan High
School 35-34, East Robertson High School 40-20, Lewis County High School 49-22, and
Memphis Business Academy 22-12, finishing the season with a 14-1 record; and
WHEREAS, in addition to claiming victory over reigning state champion Marion County,
the Mustangs defeated four region champions in the playoffs, beating teams with three Mr.
Football finalists, the 2025 Mr. Football, and last year's Mr. Football; and
WHEREAS, the Mustangs posted three shutouts for the year and held seven of fifteen
opponents to seven points or less, even after being picked to finish fifth in the region by one
preseason publication; and
WHEREAS, the members of this exceptional championship team are Tyreke Hutch,
Owen King, Zayden Connelly, Hayes Eubanks, Taylor Jones, Ayden Woods, Braylin Dearmon,
Lucas Smith, Gavin Gray, Keimonte Strayhorn, Jeramyah Cannon, Maddox Holmes, Benton
HJR0850
